-- India's TCS, HCLT slumps on earnings disappointment
-- By Abhishek Vishnoi
-- Fri Oct 17, 2014 12:00AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, Oct 17 (Reuters) - India's Tata Consultancy Services (TCS) <TCS.NS> fell as much as 8.5 percent, heading towards its biggest single day fall since May 2009 after its earnings disappointed while its sequential U.S. dollar revenue growth also lagged estimates

Analysts said TCS' 6.4 percent revenue growth from the previous quarter missed estimates for nearly 8 percent growth. Earnings also came slightly below expectations.[ID:nL3N0SB4S2]